Package com.blockwithme.util.shared.converters

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BooleanConverter<CONTEXT,E>
    BooleanConverter implements the conversion of some object type, to and from Java primitive boolean values.
    ByteConverter<CONTEXT,E>
    ByteConverter implements the conversion of some object type, to and from Java primitive byte values.
    CharConverter<CONTEXT,E>
    CharConverter implements the conversion of some object type, to and from Java primitive char values.
    ConfiguredConverter<CONTEXT,E>
    ConfiguredConverter is a Converter, that requires some additional configuration, in the form of a String.
    Converter<CONTEXT,E>
    The Base Interface for all the converter interfaces.
    Converters
    A bunch of default converters.
    DoubleConverter<CONTEXT,E>
    DoubleConverter implements the conversion of some object type, to and from Java primitive double values.
    FloatConverter<CONTEXT,E>
    FloatConverter implements the conversion of some object type, to and from Java primitive float values.
    IntConverter<CONTEXT,E>
    IntConverter implements the conversion of some object type, to and from Java primitive int values.
    LongConverter<CONTEXT,E>
    LongConverter implements the conversion of some object type, to and from Java primitive long values.
    ObjectConverter<CONTEXT,FROM,TO>
    ObjectConverter implements the conversion of some object type, to and from some other object type.
    ShortConverter<CONTEXT,E>
    ShortConverter implements the conversion of some object type, to and from Java primitive short values.
    StringConverter<CONTEXT,E>
    StringConverter implements the conversion of some object type, to and from Java String values.
